WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.140 --> 00:00:04.059
Intersectionality recognizes that our identities like race,

1
00:00:04.179 --> 00:00:04.639
gender,

2
00:00:04.980 --> 00:00:05.539
class,

3
00:00:05.780 --> 00:00:06.519
and more

4
00:00:06.699 --> 00:00:09.699
interconnect to shape our unique experiences.

5
00:00:10.890 --> 00:00:13.880
It's not about experiencing these identities separately,

6
00:00:14.130 --> 00:00:16.149
but instead as a complex whole.

7
00:00:17.270 --> 00:00:21.469
Research shows that individuals with multiple marginalized identities

8
00:00:21.770 --> 00:00:23.270
face compounded oppression

9
00:00:23.450 --> 00:00:25.709
and limited opportunities as a result.

10
00:00:26.700 --> 00:00:27.489
For example,

11
00:00:27.739 --> 00:00:30.200
women of color experience both racism

12
00:00:30.340 --> 00:00:31.260
and sexism,

13
00:00:31.489 --> 00:00:34.159
which can lead to significant health disparities.

14
00:00:34.619 --> 00:00:36.770
By understanding intersectionality,

15
00:00:36.970 --> 00:00:39.959
we can provide more empathetic and effective support.

16
00:00:40.919 --> 00:00:43.389
This allows us to respect the full complexity

17
00:00:43.389 --> 00:00:46.490
of each person's background and lived experience.

18
00:00:47.069 --> 00:00:49.830
Recognizing intersectionality is crucial

19
00:00:49.990 --> 00:00:53.250
for creating a more equitable and inclusive society.

20
00:00:53.590 --> 00:00:56.930
Are you ready to see the world through a more intersectional lens?